Package org.eclipse.mosaic.fed.application.app.api.os

Interface AgentOperatingSystem

All Superinterfaces:
CellCommunicative, Locatable, OperatingSystem, PtRoutable, Routable
All Known Implementing Classes:
AgentUnit
public interface AgentOperatingSystem extends OperatingSystem, Locatable, CellCommunicative, Routable, PtRoutable
An agent represents a person in the simulation which is able to use public transport facilities, can walk, or use private or shared vehicles for transportation. An agent does not move until its mapped application provides instructions, such as using public transport or a private car.

This interface extends the basic OperatingSystem and is implemented by the AgentUnit.

  • Method Details

    • usePrivateVehicle

      void usePrivateVehicle(String vehicleType, CandidateRoute route)
      Changes the next leg of the agent to use a private vehicle. It will spawn a new vehicle and assigns this agent to it. The Routable.getRoutingModule() should be used to calculate CandidateRoutes for such vehicle trip.

    • useSharedVehicle

      void useSharedVehicle(String vehicleId)
      Changes the next leg of the agent to use vehicle which already exists in the simulation, such as a shared vehicle or shuttle bus.

    • usePublicTransport

      void usePublicTransport(PtRoute publicTransportRoute)
      Changes the next leg(s) of the agent to use public transportation. The provided public transport route would contain one or more legs of type public transport, or walking. The PtRoutable.getPtRoutingModule() should be used to calculate such routes.

    • finishAgent

      void finishAgent()
      Removes this agent from the simulation proactively.
